This Monday, Venus moves into the sign of Aries. Plus, today – Sunday May 1, 2022 – is Beltane, the pagan and Wiccan festival celebrating the height of spring and the early days of summer. Together, these two cosmic calendar events make for a very passionate, romantic, and emotional week ahead. It’s time to be bold, confident, and hopeful about your love life. It’s time to ask them out, make a proposal, turn up the heat, go to the next level. Whatever your aspirations in love, this is a great week to put effort into making them come true. Let your tarot horoscope advise what wonderful energy could flow into your star sign’s love life this week… March 21 to April 20 Tarot card for Aries for this week: Knight of Wands Meaning: Single Aries, you could be swept off your feet by a super exciting and sexy Fire sign (Leo, Aries, Sagittarius) who wants to take you away on an adventure… up for that? The Knight of Wands brings excitement and new news to your love life- you’re ready to do different things, have an adventure together, try something new. It will refresh your bond, make you feel young and silly again, and reignite those flames of passion you yearn for. Head here for everything you need to know about being an Aries April 21 to May 21 Tarot card for Taurus for this week: Four of Swords Meaning: You just want to chill out. You want things to be quiet, calm, easy and peaceful. You want to spend your time together being low-key and relaxed, pottering, tootling about doing very little, but being happy with that. You want them to get on your speed. Single Taureans are ready for a laidback Air sign – Gemini, Libra or Aquarius. Right now, you’re feeling like you want something easy and free-flowing. No pressure or demands. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Taurus May 22 to June 21 Tarot card for Gemini for this week: Ten of Swords Meaning: You’re ready to cut ties. The Ten of Swords is a tough card about severing bonds with something that has weighed