ove and switch up the dynamic, the status quo, the usual suspects? Do it, Virgo. This is a major turning point. Actively, consciously seek to change who you speak to, how, what you expect, what you demand, what you do and how you do it. See this as a fascinating experiment! Head here for everything you need to know about being a Virgo September 24 to October 23 Tarot card for Libra for this week: Ace of Swords Meaning: You’re in the mood for a heart to heart. It could be with your partner, about your partner, or even just about your hopes/fears around your love life with a close, trusted friend. Get things off your chest, express yourself, say how you feel honestly. The Ace of Swords gives you permission to speak your truth, but also asks you to understand others’ opinions or feelings too, give them the compassion you wish for yourself and this discussion will yield great results. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Libra October 24 to November 22 Tarot card for Scorpio for this week: Nine of Cups Meaning: What is your honest heart’s desire in your love life? I ask because the Nine of Cups is a cosmic wish ‘pass’ from the Universe to manifest whatever you most want! Truly, the higher you aim, the better the outcome so please use this week to make overt moves in the direction of the love life you yearn for. Water signs (Cancer, Pisces, Scorpio) are well starred right now too. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Scorpio November 23 to December 21 Tarot card for Sagittarius for this week: Nine of Wands Meaning: Nothing is as difficult, testing, bleak or dark as it seems right now, so have faith, keep going, and make the effort to overcome the obstacles or challenges you think exist in your relationship landscape. The Nine of Wands urges you to fix things, because they can be fixed and it is worthwhile. Plain sailing is on the other side of this hump, so get past it. Fire sign friends can help inspire you – Leo, Aries and Sagittarius. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Sagittarius December 22 to January 21 Tarot card for Capricorn for this week: The High Priestess Meaning: You are ready to do some deep and personal soul searching around your love life hopes and fears. The High Priestess brings forth inner wisdom and self-awareness that can truly help you figure things out right now. Make this a week to meditate, reflect, go on mindful walks, be peaceful and think. What you come to understand will make a lasting difference to your outlook and how you approach partners or objects of affection hereonin. You are changing, do so consciously. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Capricorn January 22 to February 19 Tarot card for Aquarius for this week: Eight of Coins Meaning: Don’t give up. Don’t throw the towel in. Don’t walk away or abandon this hope/relationship/flirtation just because things haven’t gone your way or it’s taking more effort than you thought it would. The Eight of Coins urges you to persist, work on it, take time to talk and understand and do your part to make this whole enterprise a healthier, happier space. If you’re single, a hardworking Earth sign looks just the ticket – Capricorn, Virgo or Taurus. Head here for everything you need to know about being an Aquarius February 20 to March 20 Tarot card for Pisces for this week: Justice Meaning: You will be proven correct and in the right about something that felt unfair or unkind, and which you’ve borne the brunt of. You will be vindicated and thanked for your dignity and resilience in this matter. Act graciously. Enjoy the moment, but don’t rub anyone’s nose in it. Let the relationship return to an even keel, and heal. If you’re single, a smart and charitable Libra is making eyes at you – do look up and notice them! Head here for everything you need to know about being a Pisces Your daily Metro.co.uk horoscope is here every morning, seven days a week (yes, including weekends!). To check yo